article.headline: Wichita St. 65, Centenary 44
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. -- Garrett Stutz scored 22 points and fellow freshman Toure Murry added 15 to lead Wichita State over Centenary 65-44 on Monday night. Stutz, a 7-footer making his first start for the Shockers (2-1), scored 15 of his game-high total in the first half on 7-of-10 shooting from the field. Murry did all of his scoring in the second half. Centenary (1-4) was led by Chase Adams with 13 points. Wichita State led throughout, but the Gents came within 24-20 at halftime on a 3-pointer by Nick Stallings just before the buzzer. But Murry scored 13 points on three 3-pointers and two layups to help the Shockers widen the lead to 39-28 in the first 5 minutes of the second half. Wichita State shot 53 percent from the field for the game while Centenary shot just 31 percent.
